<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 11:59PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Heard and
western Coweta Counties through 1230 AM EDT...
At 1159 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Franklin, moving
northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Franklin, Centralhatchee, Corinth, Powers Crossroads, Handy and Plant
Wansley.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
